        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 5 at 1:16AM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 116 AM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 12
miles west of Broadus, moving north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Olive.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
